Copyright Garbage;copyright-garbage.yml` file allows to define which Copyright statements are to be considered as garbage, like any invalid findings from a scanner. This can be done by literal strings or regular expression patterns. The *evaluator* and reporter* take the file as optional input. See the [example](#ex;copyright-garbage.yml`, or pass a custom file via the;copyright-garbage-file` option of the *evaluator* or *reporter*. For example:;copyright-garbage-file $ORT_CONFIG_DIR/copyright-garbage.yml;copyright-garbage.yml';copyright-garbage.yml">{Example}</CodeBlock>
